Frontier Airlines plans to charge up to $100 for passengers who wish to store hand luggage on their flight.
Frontier Airlines intends to charge up to $100 for one piece of hand luggage and $2 for coffee or lemonade, even if the announcement on Wednesday indicated that passengers could keep the whole can.
The new fee applies to hand luggage in the luggage compartment above the seat, small pockets under the seat are still free of charge.
Frontier stated that if the fee is paid in advance, 25 US dollars will be charged and 100 US dollars will be charged to travellers who only paid at the gate.
Frontier spokeswoman Kate O'Malley said the $100 fee is aimed at moving travelers to take care of the payment in advance.
