However, most of them have so far left their hands on hand baggage charges.
Spirit Airlines Inc. was the first to charge for hand baggage three years ago and later followed Allegiant Air, also a low-cost airliner.
The only other airline with such a fee is the Hungarian Wizz Air, explained airline consultant Jay Sorensen, who closely monitors the additional charges.
In a December 2011 report, he estimated that the Spirit hand baggage fee would bring in $50 million a year.
