The investigation revealed that Ditta regularly used Class A drugs after traces of cocaine had been found in his hair, wallet and credit cards during tests.
Over a period of eight months between January and August 2011, he attempted to obtain illicit information about the arrest of two men on behalf of Scarborough and one of his partners.
All four suspects were then monitored by the police as part of a major investigation into heroin and cocaine trafficking in Lancashire, Cumbria, Merseyside, Berkshire and West Yorkshire.
